            hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee is a user interface for displaying online
            documentation such as reference manuals, tutorials, and
            help systems.  Most online documents are prepared using
            nnnnrrrrooooffffffff and the mmmmmmmm macros, but any ASCII file can be
            browsed.

            hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee provides commands for:

               - listing available documents ("card catalog"),

               - moving sequentially through a document,

               - displaying a document's section headings
                 ("Table of Contents"),

               - jumping from the Table of Contents directly to any
                 selected section,

               - jumping to related documents using hypertext links
                 ("references"),

               - remembering locations so they can be returned to
                 ("bookmarks"),

               - retracing a path through a series of documents
                 ("return stack").

            The overhead of learning to use hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee is
            sufficiently low that most users do not need to read
            this manual page:

               - The command syntax is similar to a small subset of
                 vvvviiii or eeeemmmmaaaaccccssss.  The interface changes depending on
                 your EEEEDDDDIIIITTTTOOOORRRR variable.




