            An online Administrator's Guide tells how to create a
            browsing system based on hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee.  In a typical
            application, the person providing the documents would:

              1.  Format the documents using nnnnrrrrooooffffffff and a special
                  version of the mmmmmmmm macros.  The macros adjust the
                  document's appearance for more effective online
                  browsing and mark section headings and references
                  so hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee can find them.

              2.  Write a short document called a Catalog.  The
                  Catalog is the starting point for users to find
                  information; it describes the documents and gives
                  their filenames.

              3.  Create a short shell script to call hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee with
                  application-specific parameters, such as the list
                  of directories where the documents are stored
                  (see the PPPPAAAARRRRAAAAMMMMEEEETTTTEEEERRRRSSSS section below).

            This manual page describes the basics of hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee;
            complete documentation is available by calling hhhhyyyybbbbrrrroooowwwwsssseeee
            without any parameters and walking through the
            tutorial.  The tutorial and help screens will direct
            you to an online Administrators' Guide that tells how
            to format documents for browsing.


